Rewrite `docker buildx build` → `docker build` in container-build/build-image.sh
so the script runs under podman (via alias docker=podman) without needing the
Docker buildx plugin.

Context:
  scitrera's build-image.sh invokes `docker buildx build ...`. podman does not
  have a `buildx` subcommand — BuildKit features are built into `podman build`
  natively (including `RUN --mount=type=cache,...` which Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
  relies on heavily). All the flags build-image.sh actually passes
  (-f, -t, --build-arg, --label, --target, --no-cache, context path) are valid
  for plain `docker build` as well, so dropping `buildx` is a pure no-op on
  Docker and a compatibility fix on podman.

  The `RUN --mount=type=cache` instructions in Dockerfile.sglang-nightly were
  verified to work on podman 5.4.2 / buildah 1.39.3 locally — the uv-cache and
  ccache mounts will persist across rebuilds in podman's cache store the same
  way BuildKit handles them in Docker.

Apply to: container-build/build-image.sh in the local clone of
scitrera/cuda-containers. Applied by scripts/build_sm121_image.sh alongside
the Dockerfile patch and the sgl-kernel source patch.

--- a/container-build/build-image.sh
+++ b/container-build/build-image.sh
@@ -259,7 +259,7 @@
 fi

 # Build the docker command
-BUILD_CMD=(docker buildx build)
+BUILD_CMD=(docker build)

 # Add --no-cache if requested
 $NO_CACHE && BUILD_CMD+=(--no-cache)
